Nexa3D xCE Black Photoplastic Materials

High performance polymer for producing end-use plastic parts and injection molding tools in minutes. Nexa3D’s new material is a single cure polymer that delivers higher flexural strength compared to those typically achieved only in dual cure cyanate ester resins. Nexa3D xCE Black has excellent isotropic properties and exhibit long-term environmental stability.

xCE-Black is used to produce injection molding tools for a wide range of thermoplastic polymers including PP, PE, HDPE and PETG. Molds printed from xCE-Black were successfully injected hundreds of times at temperatures between 230°C and 280°C without any visible mold temperature degradation or adhesion, and without the use of any mold release agents.

    Property Test Value
    Tensile Modulus ASTM D638 1620 MPa
    Ultimate Tensile Strength ASTM D638 80 MPa
    Tensile Elongation at Break ASTM D638 8%
    Flex Modulus ASTM D790 3250 MPa
    Flex Strength ASTM D790 135 MPa
    Hardness (shore D) ASTM D2240 90
    Notched Izod ASTM D256 20 J/m
